!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

wise /waɪz/

(wiser,wisest) 

1. ADJ A wise person is able to use their experience and knowledge in order to make sensible decisions and judgments. 有智慧的 

例： She has the air of a wise woman. 她有才女的气质。 

2. wisely ADV 英明地 [ADV with v] 

例： The three of us stood around the machine nodding wisely. 我们3个人站在机器周围，明白地点点头。 

3. ADJ A wise action or decision is sensible. (行动或决定) 明智的 

例： It's never wise to withhold evidence. 隐瞒证据绝不明智。 

例： She had made a very wise decision. 她作出了一个非常明智的决定。 

4. wisely ADV 明智地 

例： They've invested their money wisely. 他们明智地把钱做了投资。 

5. N way, manner, fashion, or respect (esp in the phrases any wise, in no wise ) 情况 [archaic]

</div>

